3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses algorithms for solving the probabilistic CI implication problem, which involves solving linear programs and may be of interest to researchers in data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses probabilistic conditional independence, which is a topic in information theory. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses validation algorithms for CI statements, which may be relevant to researchers in systems and control.
